Basic knowledges about cellular and molecular aspects of immune system are given. Also we explain possibilities for evaluation of immune system function and treatment in clinical settings.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To get basic knowledges for the further studies in clinical medicine.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course, within the syllabus, a student:  1. is acquainted with the basic but up-to-date knowledge about the immune system; 2. knows and understands the cellular and molecular mechanisms of the immune system; 3. knows the general properties of the diseases and pathological conditions which are immune system related, is able to understand the corresponding immune processes in the human organism, is capable to give examples of most common disorders in immune system; 4. knows how to evaluate the status of the immune system and corresponding options for immune modulation, knows immunological methods and their use in diagnosis; 5. is able to navigate in the modern medical literature on the field of immunology, is able to find specialized scientific articles and to complement its own knowledge about the immunology
